00:07:34:080000.Dialogue: and see if there's a blunder I overlooked.

00:07:38:190000.Speaker: Leonard
00:07:38:190000.Dialogue: Here you go. You owe me another two dollars. The price of moo shu pork went up.

00:07:44:020000.Speaker: Howard
00:07:44:020000.Dialogue: It's getting tougher and tougher to be a bad Jew.

00:07:49:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:07:49:050000.Dialogue: Here you go, Penny. Shrimp with lobster sauce.

00:07:54:210000.Dialogue: Really, how much? Whatever. $10, $11. Which is it, $10 or $11?

00:08:08:230000.Speaker: Howard
00:08:08:230000.Dialogue: He was just wondering if he wore skintight jeans and a tank top if he'd get his shrimp lo mein for free.

00:08:17:080000.Speaker: Penny
00:08:17:080000.Dialogue: What are you saying? That I'm using my body to get dinner? That I'm some kind of Chinese food prostitute?

00:08:25:160000.Speaker: Howard

00:08:28:070000.Speaker: Penny

00:08:40:060000.Speaker: Howard
00:08:40:060000.Dialogue: He has a nervous bladder when he's stressed out.

00:08:58:030000.Speaker: Penny
00:08:58:030000.Dialogue: Yes, and I'm having some. I'm having takeout food. You're damn right it's okay. I've been having leftovers at the restaurant for like four days, and I wanted something different. So sue me.

00:09:06:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:06:200000.Dialogue: Forgive me, but that would be the very definition of a frivolous lawsuit.

00:09:12:160000.Speaker: Penny
00:09:12:160000.Dialogue: I will pay you back as soon as I can. You just have to give me more time.

00:09:18:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:18:170000.Dialogue: You seem under pressure. Did I not lend you a sufficient amount? Because I can give you more.

00:09:23:150000.Speaker: Penny
00:09:23:150000.Dialogue: You know, you would just love that, wouldn't you?

00:09:29:070000.Speaker: Penny
00:09:29:070000.Dialogue: You would just love to open up your little snake can and throw some money at the girl who can't pay her bills.

00:09:52:150000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:52:150000.Dialogue: In case either of you have larceny in your heart, you should know that I've moved my money out of the snake can.

00:10:01:160000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:01:160000.Dialogue: But if you're ever short, there's always a couple of 50s in Green Lantern's ass.

00:10:19:180000.Speaker: Penny
00:10:19:180000.Dialogue: When I didn't pay my bill, the Department of Water and Power thought I would enjoy the ambience.

00:10:25:230000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:25:230000.Dialogue: Yeah, they're very considerate that way.

00:10:28:180000.Speaker: Penny
00:10:28:180000.Dialogue: I used Sheldon's money to pay my rent. Then I had like $14 left over.

00:10:37:020000.Speaker: Penny
00:10:37:020000.Dialogue: Put it back in your pocket, or I'll find some other place to put it.

00:10:41:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:41:140000.Dialogue: Back in the pocket it goes. You do understand Sheldon really doesn't care when he gets the money back. It's actually one of the few idiosyncrasies that doesn't make you want to... kill him.

00:10:53:220000.Speaker: Penny
00:10:53:220000.Dialogue: Yeah, well, that's not really my big problem.

00:10:56:090000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:56:090000.Dialogue: So you're a little behind on your bills. Everybody gets behind on their bills.

00:10:59:190000.Speaker: Penny
00:10:59:190000.Dialogue: I know, it's just... This wasn't the plan. It wasn't supposed to go this way.

00:11:06:230000.Speaker: Penny
00:11:06:230000.Dialogue: Waitress for six months and then become a movie star.

00:11:18:030000.Speaker: Leonard
00:11:18:030000.Dialogue: It's probably not as bad as you think. Let's take a look. Maybe we can find some corners to cut. Here's something. If you don't have electricity, then you probably don't need cable.

00:11:37:130000.Speaker: Penny
00:11:37:130000.Dialogue: No, I can't give up my acting classes. I'm a professional actress.

00:11:41:220000.Speaker: Leonard
00:11:41:220000.Dialogue: You've had an acting job where you got paid?

00:11:44:070000.Speaker: Penny
00:11:44:070000.Dialogue: That is not the definition of professional.

00:11:51:000000.Speaker: Leonard
00:11:51:000000.Dialogue: Actually, it kind of... Let's keep looking. What's $1,800 to the Los Angeles County Superior Court?

00:12:02:220000.Speaker: Leonard
00:12:02:220000.Dialogue: Nothing? It sounds like you got caught speeding going 4,000 miles an hour.

00:12:14:140000.Speaker: Penny
00:12:14:140000.Dialogue: He got arrested for taking a whiz on a cop car.

00:12:20:190000.Speaker: Penny
00:12:20:190000.Dialogue: He had a bunch of outstanding tickets and a bench warrant, so I, you know, I paid his fines.

00:12:29:070000.Speaker: Leonard
00:12:29:070000.Dialogue: And that's based on the inherent credit-worthiness of people who get drunk and urinate on police vehicles?

00:12:36:080000.Speaker: Penny
00:12:36:080000.Dialogue: Leonard, I'm not gonna call up Kurt and ask him for money.

00:12:49:110000.Speaker: Leonard
00:12:49:110000.Dialogue: You don't want to do that.

00:12:53:040000.Speaker: Leonard
00:12:53:040000.Dialogue: Moving is a big deal. You have to go to the supermarket and get boxes, and if they're not clean, your books smell like melons, and it's like...

00:13:05:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:05:020000.Dialogue: Why don't you just get a roommate and stay here?

00:13:09:230000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:09:230000.Dialogue: I'm sure the guy living with Sheldon wouldn't mind moving in with you.

00:13:15:180000.Speaker: Penny
00:13:15:180000.Dialogue: Leonard, honey, if we started living together, I wouldn't be able to keep my hands off you.

00:13:26:230000.Speaker: Penny
00:13:26:230000.Dialogue: And you thought my acting lessons were a waste of money.

00:13:35:190000.Speaker: Howard
00:13:35:190000.Dialogue: This Moo Shu pork's burning a hole through my duodenum.

00:13:41:110000.Speaker: Raj
00:13:41:110000.Dialogue: Leviticus 11:03  Only that which parteth the hoof and cheweth the cud among the beasts shall ye eat.

00:13:50:050000.Speaker: Howard
00:13:50:050000.Dialogue: Do I mock you with the Bhagavad-Gita every time you scarf down a Whopper?

00:13:59:110000.Speaker: Raj
00:13:59:110000.Dialogue: - We're on a quest through the Valley of Fire to acquire the sacred crown.

00:14:03:160000.Speaker: Howard
00:14:03:160000.Dialogue: You want the Valley of Fire? It's right here.

00:14:08:060000.Speaker: Leonard
00:14:08:060000.Dialogue: You guys want to go on a real live quest?

00:14:17:000000.Speaker: Leonard
00:14:17:000000.Dialogue: Do you guys remember Penny's ex-boyfriend Kurt?

00:14:24:060000.Speaker: Leonard
00:14:24:060000.Dialogue: Turns out he owes Penny a lot of money, and I'm gonna go get it from him. Who's with me?

00:14:36:030000.Speaker: Leonard
00:14:36:030000.Dialogue: Really? You're just gonna let me go by myself?

00:14:46:070000.Speaker: Leonard
00:14:46:070000.Dialogue: You guys are unbelievable. You play a game to simulate adventure, but when there's real adventure out there in the real world, you just wimp out.

00:14:53:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:53:110000.Dialogue: Do you not recall the last time we visited this gentleman, we returned home without pants?

00:15:20:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:20:140000.Dialogue: Say hi to Kurt for us.

00:15:24:060000.Speaker: Leonard
00:15:24:060000.Dialogue: Excuse me. When Frodo left the Shire to take the one ring to Mordor, didn't Samwise, Pippin and Merry go with him?

00:15:31:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:31:180000.Dialogue: They had a terrible time of it.

00:15:36:010000.Speaker: Raj
00:15:36:010000.Dialogue: Plus, no one stole their pants.

00:15:39:150000.Speaker: Leonard
00:15:39:150000.Dialogue: Fine. Enjoy your little game. I'll make this quest on my own.

00:15:44:040000.Speaker: Howard
00:15:44:040000.Dialogue: Wait. Take a jacket. It's shpritzing a little.

00:15:49:100000.Speaker: Leonard
00:15:49:100000.Dialogue: You guys suck. Come on, please? He's so big.

00:15:59:100000.Speaker: Leonard
00:15:59:100000.Dialogue: Is everyone clear on the plan?

00:16:01:050000.Speaker: Howard
00:16:01:050000.Dialogue: Koothrappali's going to wet himself, I'm gonna throw up, Sheldon's gonna run away, and you're going to die.

00:16:11:030000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:11:030000.Dialogue: Guys, there are four of us and one of him.

00:16:13:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:13:140000.Dialogue: Which means his triumph will be even larger.

00:16:17:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:17:120000.Dialogue: Minstrels will write songs about him.

00:16:20:080000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:20:080000.Dialogue: How about this? I'll do the talking. You just stand behind me and try to look formidable.

00:16:31:050000.Speaker: Raj
00:16:31:050000.Dialogue: I should've peed before we left.

00:16:42:200000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:42:200000.Dialogue: I don't really go by Lenny, but that's okay.

00:16:46:080000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:46:080000.Dialogue: You remember Sheldon, Howard and Raj.

00:16:58:090000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:58:090000.Dialogue: Here it is. Penny's in kind of a financial jam, and the money that you owe her would go a long way to solving her problems.

00:17:05:030000.Speaker: Kurt
00:17:05:030000.Dialogue: She sent you to get it from me?

00:17:06:180000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:06:180000.Dialogue: No, no, she's too proud to ask for the money. I, on the other hand, feel you should honor your debt.

00:17:17:150000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:17:150000.Dialogue: Feel is a kind of a... it's a strong word. I just think it would be a nice gesture on your part.

00:17:23:000000.Speaker: Kurt
00:17:23:000000.Dialogue: She'll get it when she gets it.

00:17:29:090000.Speaker: Howard
00:17:29:090000.Dialogue: Well, there you go. Problem solved.

00:17:33:020000.Speaker: Raj
00:17:33:020000.Dialogue: A successful quest. Now let's go find a gas station with a clean bathroom.

00:17:37:160000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:37:160000.Dialogue: No, the problem isn't solved. - He just blew us off.

00:17:39:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:39:140000.Dialogue: - I've got it. He didn't remember me because the last time we met, I was in a Halloween costume.

00:17:50:210000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:50:210000.Dialogue: You can leave if you want to. I'm gonna see this through.

00:18:00:210000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:00:210000.Dialogue: I guess, technically, that was my fault.

00:18:09:150000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:09:150000.Dialogue: I'm not leaving here without Penny's money.

00:18:18:040000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:18:040000.Dialogue: I have right on my side.

00:18:24:150000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:24:150000.Dialogue: And I'm wearing cargo shorts under my pants.

00:18:30:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:30:070000.Dialogue: Congratulations. You may not have succeed in getting cash, but you did secure a formal acknowledgment of the debt.

00:18:42:140000.Speaker: Howard
00:18:42:140000.Dialogue: Maybe we should have your head notarized.

00:18:48:120000.Speaker: Raj
00:18:48:120000.Dialogue: If anybody cares, I still have to pee.

00:19:04:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:19:04:170000.Dialogue: It's kind of a fashionable look these days.

00:19:07:230000.Speaker: Penny
00:19:07:230000.Dialogue: Maybe if you're working on a tuna boat.

00:19:11:110000.Speaker: Penny
00:19:11:110000.Dialogue: - Sheldon, here is your money. Thank you very much. It helped a lot.

00:19:20:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:20:030000.Dialogue: Darn. I can't seem to get the hang of that.

00:19:24:000000.Speaker: Leonard
00:19:24:000000.Dialogue: I know it's none of my business, but where did the money come from?

00:19:27:090000.Speaker: Penny
00:19:27:090000.Dialogue: Well, I cut back my expenses like you said and picked up a few more hours at the restaurant, but the biggest thing was, out of the blue, Kurt shows up and gives me the money he owes me.

00:19:42:160000.Speaker: Penny
00:19:42:160000.Dialogue: He said he was feeling guilty and wanted to do what was right.

00:19:52:000000.Speaker: Leonard
00:19:52:000000.Dialogue: Did he give any reason as to why he came to this moral epiphany?

00:19:58:020000.Speaker: Penny
00:19:58:020000.Dialogue: I just think he's really changed. We're having dinner tomorrow night, and I get to wear my new beret.

00:20:18:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:20:18:180000.Dialogue: The true hero doesn't seek adulation. He fights for right and justice simply because it's his nature.

00:20:25:070000.Speaker: Leonard
00:20:25:070000.Dialogue: Penny's hooking up with her jerk of an ex-boyfriend, and I have indelible ink on my forehead!

00:20:31:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:20:31:100000.Dialogue: That's your badge of honor... your warrior's wound, if you will. I was wrong. Minstrels will write songs about you.

00:20:43:220000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:20:43:220000.Dialogue: There once was a brave lad named Leonard

00:20:51:080000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:20:51:080000.Dialogue: He faced a fearsome giant While Raj just wanted to pee
